title: POS - cannot start
text: 1. Check if the POSCONFIG database is empty. If so, follow this guideline POS won't start - POSCONFIG is empty 2. Check if the POS has C++ Redistributable 2005 installed. If not download and install from here: https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=26347 Run vcredist.exe (search for it. Can usually be found under /user/appdata/local/windows/… (remember to turn on show hidden files, or you won't be able to find it) If it still doesn't work, send the case through to Development (Rene). Remember to give him Client ID and Teamviewer ID.
description:

  1. 2. Check if the POS has C++ Redistributable 2005 installed. 

  

If not download and install from here:   

https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=26347

title: POS - login on PC
text: If the POS PC hasn't logged in automatically (after restart / startup), use justenter as a password with the username User If that does not work, restart the machine. If that does not work, create a case and send it to Technique.

title: POS - login not working
text: If the login on the POS doesn't work (the sales assistant types in their number, clicks the green button and nothing happens), you can set the POS program to run as admin. Shutdown the POS program through Task Manager Right-click on the DdDPOS icon -> Properties -> Advanced -> tick Run as administrator -> OK -> OK Restart POS
description:
If the login on the POS doesn't work (the sales assistant types in their number, clicks the green button and nothing happens), you can set the POS program to run as admin. 

  

 

  

  1. Shutdown the POS program through Task Manager 

  

  1. Right-click on the DdDPOS icon -> Properties -> Advanced -> tick Run as administrator -> OK -> OK 

  

  1. Restart POS

title: PDF - open report on POS shows only a grey, blank window
text: Log into POS Click on Screen with Wrench button Choose store and machine Choose Adv. Configuration Scroll down and check UseOwnPDFViewer. If it's set to 0, set it to 1 Scroll down to the bottom and click Save, then Close. Click cancle sale Type Reload in the Shop Assistant field and then the green button If this does not work, you can also do it through the SQL Database: Open Microsoft SQL Server Management Studio Log into database Open Databases, POSCONFIG, dbo.StoreConfiguration Locate UseOwnPDFViewer and set Value to 1. Reload or restart POS and try again. If this still does no work, restart the PC.
description:
Log into POS 

  

Click on Screen with Wrench button 

  

 

  

Choose store and machine 

  

 

  

Choose Adv. Configuration 

  

 

  

Scroll down and check UseOwnPDFViewer. If it's set to 0, set it to 1 

  

 

  

Scroll down to the bottom and click Save, then Close. 

  

 

  

Click cancle sale 

  

 

  

Type Reload in the Shop Assistant field and then the green button 

  

 

  

If this does not work, you can also do it through the SQL Database: 

  

Open Microsoft SQL Server Management Studio 

  

Log into database 

  

Open Databases, POSCONFIG, dbo.StoreConfiguration 

  

Locate UseOwnPDFViewer and set Value to 1. 

  

Reload or restart POS and try again. 

  

  

 

  

  

If this still does no work, restart the PC.

title: POS - PC is dead (black screen)
text: If the client says that the POS is dead and they have tried turning it on as usual, ask them to pull the power plug and leave it off for 30 seconds before plugging it in again. If this doesn't work, ask them to repeat the procedure for 10 minutes. After that, it should start again. If they haven't tried to push any buttons, tell them to find the on off switch (either beneath the screen or on the side) and turn it on there.
description:
If the client says that the POS is dead and they have tried turning it on as usual, ask them to pull the power plug and leave it off for 30 seconds before plugging it in again. 

  

If this doesn't work, ask them to repeat the procedure for 10 minutes. After that, it should start again. 

  

If they haven't tried to push any buttons, tell them to find the on off switch (either beneath the screen or on the side) and turn it on there.

title: POS - Reload / Restart
text: For most changes to take effect, you need to either Reload or Restart the POS: Reload will simply recheck with the database. Wait for the clock to start running again and it's ready. Restart will restart the entire POS program (e.g. shut it down and start it up again).
description:
For most changes to take effect, you need to either Reload or Restart the POS: 

  

 

  

Reload will simply recheck with the database. Wait for the clock to start running again and it's ready. 

  

  

 

  

Restart will restart the entire POS program (e.g. shut it down and start it up again).

title: POS - Search parameters
text: These are the 4 search parameters shown when a client performs a search on the POS 1. To change the order or replace one with another one, click on Screen with wrench. Everything above the black line is shown in that order, everything below is not. To change order, grab e.g. Article Number with the mouse and pull it down. Release and save. To exchange one for another, grab e.g. Season with the mouse and pull it above the black line, then arrange it in the order you want it in. Note that e.g. Size (the last parameter before the black line) is then pulled beneath the line and will no longer be visible in the search. Click Save -> Close and reload the POS

title: POS - Search parameters missing
text: If the customer gets this window when trying to search for items from the POS, this can be caused by the search parameters not being loaded correctly. Click DdDAdmin Choose the affected POS (if there is more than one). Click Search parameters Reorder one from above to below the black line. Save Click Close Click Cancel Sale Type Reload in the Sales Assistant field Click green button Log in again and repeat the reorder of the search parameters, setting them back to their original setup, and reload again. This should fix it.
description:
If the customer gets this window when trying to search for items from the POS, this can be caused by the search parameters not being loaded correctly. 

  

 

  

  

  • Click DdDAdmin  

  •  

  

  • Choose the affected POS (if there is more than one). 

  

  • Click Search parameters

This should fix it.

title: POS - won't start - POSCONFIG is empty
text: Open Microsoft SQL Server Management Studio If the Database POSCONFIG is empty, or says POSCONFIG (restoring…) (can't be expanded), then do as follows 1. First make certain that all processes in connection with the POS are closed. 2. Right-click on the taskbar and open the Task Manager 3. End any processes called POS or DdD. 4. Open SQL Server Configuration Manager 5. Stop the server and start it again. You may have to repeat this process a few times. 6. Go back to Microsoft SQL Server Management Studio. 7. Rightclick on POSCONFIg, choose Task, Restore, Database 8. Click the Radio button in front of From Device and then the three dots … 9. Click Add 10. If there are a lot of files in the Backup folder, you can choose the latest by opening C:\\Program Files\Microsoft SQL Server\MSSQL10_50.SQLEXPRESS\MSSQL\Backup To be on the safe side, open Windows Explorer and find the backup file there to check the date of the file. If the file is older than a few days, it is not recommended to import it and forward the ticket to 2nd Line instead. 11. Locate the last Backup file done. It will almost always be called POSConfig.bak. 12. Click on the appropriate file and click OK. 13. Click OK 14. Tick the Restore checkbox and click OK 15. If the restore was successful, you get this: 16. Click OK. If it wasn't successful, close down the SQL Server Configuration Manager, open it again and repeat the process.
description:
Open Microsoft SQL Server Management Studio 

  

If the Database POSCONFIG is empty, or says POSCONFIG (restoring…) (can't be expanded), then do as follows 

  

 

  

  1. 1. First make certain that all processes in connection with the POS are closed. 

  

  1. 2. Right-click on the taskbar and open the Task Manager 

  

 

  

  1. 3. End any processes called POS or DdD. 

  

  1. 4. Open SQL Server Configuration Manager 

  

 

  

  1. 5. Stop the server and start it again. You may have to repeat this process a few times. 

  

  1. 6. Go back to Microsoft SQL Server Management Studio. 

  

  1. 7. Rightclick on POSCONFIg, choose Task, Restore, Database 

  

 

  

 8. Click the Radio button in front of From Device and then the three dots …  

  

 

  1. 9. Click Add 

  

 

  

  1. 10. If there are a lot of files in the Backup folder, you can choose the latest by opening 

  

C:\\Program Files\Microsoft SQL Server\MSSQL10_50.SQLEXPRESS\MSSQL\Backup


To be on the safe side, open Windows Explorer and find the backup file there to check the date of the file. If the file is older than a few days, it is not recommended to import it and forward the ticket to 2nd Line instead.

  

  1. 11. Locate the last Backup file done. It will almost always be called POSConfig.bak. 

  

  1. 12. Click on the appropriate file and click OK. 

  

 

  

  1. 13. Click OK 

  

 

  

  1. 14. Tick the Restore checkbox and click OK 

  

 

  

  1. 15. If the restore was successful, you get this: 

  

 

  

  1. 16. Click OK. 

  

If it wasn't successful, close down the SQL Server Configuration Manager, open it again and repeat the process.

title: POS-How to convert POS into RIAB
text: When we receive an order to setup a new POS for a butik,The frist thing is to install a DdDPos programme on the new POS. The installation process is done by selecting a normal/general POS programme. The setup for a general POS normally look like this when we click on DdD in the POS. We have a lot of customers that have subscription for DdD RIAB and the settings on the POS must be changed to RIAB for that particular customer. The procedure to do it is as follows. Go to customers DdD admin and advanced configuration.In this example I am considering customer number/Klient id 819059. Go to EDI tools editoobox @ root.login (dddretail.com) Login with your details username support and password dddsupp Search for customer advanced configuration menu from DdD admin Enter the password ddd+2016 in order to make changes in configuration Search for 2 paramenters Show Item management and large accounts and change its value to 1 as shown below. Save the settings by selecting save button at the end of the page Run a reload command on the kasse in the clerk menu and restart the computer in order to make the changes happen. After reloading POS program the customer can now see all the setttings/menus for a RIAB in POS.
description:
When we receive an order to setup a new POS for a butik,The frist thing is to install a DdDPos programme on the new POS.
The installation process is done by selecting a normal/general POS programme.

The setup for a general POS normally look like this when we click on DdD in the POS.


We have a lot of customers that have subscription for DdD RIAB and the settings on the POS must be changed to RIAB for that particular customer.

The procedure to do it is as follows.

Go to customers DdD admin and advanced configuration.In this example I am considering customer number/Klient id 819059.
Go to EDI tools editoobox @ root.login (dddretail.com)
Login with your details  username support and password dddsupp

Search for customer 



advanced configuration menu from DdD admin


Enter the password ddd+2016 in order to make changes in configuration
Search for 2 paramenters Show Item management and large accounts and change its value to 1 as shown below.



Save the settings by selecting save button at the end of the page



Run a reload command on the kasse in the clerk menu and restart the computer in order to make the changes happen.
After reloading POS program the customer can now see all the setttings/menus for a RIAB in POS.

title: POS - hangs after purchase - no receipt coming out
text: If the Pos hangs after every purchase, you can try this. Open CMD as administrator and type in sfc /scannow and press enter This will start a scan that looks for error in windows registry and will attempt to fix these errors if found
description:

title: Exchange label instead of receipt.
text: If the shop prefers to receive an exchange label instead of an exchange receipt during the sales process, you will need to update the 'ChangeLabelsInsteadOfNote' setting to 1 in the DdD Admin system. The button on the POS Program will not changed, but when choosing the "Exchange Note" button, the label printer will print an exchange label.
description: If the shop prefers to receive an exchange label instead of an exchange receipt during the sales process, you will need to update the 'ChangeLabelsInsteadOfNote' setting to 1 in the DdD Admin system. The button on the POS Program will not changed, but when choosing the "Exchange Note" button, the label printer will print an exchange label.

title: Exchange label with variable date pop-up window on POS
text: During the sales process, If a store wants to print exchange labels on POS with a pop up window where the clerk can choose and set up a variable date regarding that sale. In such case,settings needs to be updated in DdD admin for the following parametre and the value should be updated to 2. After changing the value,click on save button in DdD admin and make a reload on POS. Now when the clerk clicks on byttebon button,a pop window should appear as shown in the screenshot where a variable date can be selected as desired by the store.

title: Buttons are messed up on POS
text: It can happen that the store contacts us regarding strange texts on the POS buttons as shown in the screenshot. Normally, it can be resolved by restoring language settings in the POS programme. The solution in such case is Close the POS Program by 999 and password 70223010 Open C Drive Select folder POS Select program Select bin Select debug Search for application RestorelanguageDB.exe and run it. Wait for update Open POS program and all should be ok. The path is shown in the below screenshot.

title: Database suspect (2ND LINE ONLY!)
text: If the POS or POSconfig databases are in the state "suspect" Execute these queries: EXEC sp_resetstatus POS; ALTER DATABASE [POS] SET EMERGENCY DBCC checkdb(POS) ALTER DATABASE POS SET SINGLE_USER WITH ROLLBACK IMMEDIATE DBCC CheckDB (POS, REPAIR_ALLOW_DATA_LOSS) ALTER DATABASE POS SET MULTI_USER and refresh, it should be back in the default state afterwards. -pictures pending
description:
If the POS or POSconfig databases are in the state "suspect"


Execute these queries: 


EXEC sp_resetstatus POS;

ALTER DATABASE [POS] SET EMERGENCY

DBCC checkdb(POS)

ALTER DATABASE POS SET SINGLE_USER WITH ROLLBACK IMMEDIATE

DBCC CheckDB (POS, REPAIR_ALLOW_DATA_LOSS)

ALTER DATABASE POS SET MULTI_USER


and refresh, it should be back in the default state afterwards. 


-pictures pending

title: Kamo antivirus makes POS programme hangs frequently
text: There can be different background progammes that blocks the pos programme to function properly and it needs to be restarted from task manager everytime which is unacceptable. KAMO is one of the antivirus programme that somehow is downloaded on the customer pc and makes problem when the POS programme is in use. The solution in such case is to delete the Kamo programme from control panel/Add-remove program. Please note that the task must be scheduled before or after the store opening times.
description:
There can be different background progammes that blocks the pos programme to function properly and it needs to be restarted from task manager everytime which is unacceptable.


KAMO is one of the antivirus programme that somehow is downloaded on the customer pc and makes problem when the POS programme is in use.

The solution in such case is to delete the Kamo programme from control panel/Add-remove program.

Please note that the task must be scheduled before or after the store opening times.

title: POS - Sale employee button is not active
text: To activate the Sale employee button on the POS (under Payment / Alternative Payment options), go to the Adv. Configuration, locate the PersonelTransferStock field and enter the client ID: Save and reload and the button will be available. Keep in mind, that the client must be created in Backoffice and the auto-update must be activated by BO.dev.support.
